# MCP reference (for Composer / Agent citations)

Treat the **indexed Cursor Doc "MCP"** (`modelcontextprotocol.io`) as authoritative. This rule is a **short mnemonic**ŌĆönot a spec replacement.

## Transport (local servers here)

This repository implements **stdio** MCP servers (`extras/mcp-rtk-server/`, legacy JS stub): JSON-RPC messages delimited/framed over **stdin / stdout**. **stderr** is reserved for diagnostics; never write MCP frames to stderr.

The **`@modelcontextprotocol/server`** `StdioServerTransport` abstracts the MCP lifecycle so your tool code stays at the **tools/register** semantic level.

## JSON-RPC mindset

MCP inherits **JSON-RPC 2.0** request/response symmetry: each request carries `jsonrpc`, `id`, `method`, optional `params`. Clients call methods such as **`tools/list`** and **`tools/call`** once capabilities are negotiated.

Canonical read: **`https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/latest`** (see *Lifecycle*, *Tools*).

### Typical handshake pattern (mental model)

1. Client capability probe / session initialization per MCP lifecycle section of the indexed docs (`initialize`, `notifications/initialized`, etc.).
2. Client lists tools: **`tools/list`** returns registered tool schemas.
3. Client invokes **`tools/call`** with `{ "name": "run_rtk_command", "arguments": { "command": "npm install -D lodash" } }`.
4. Server returns structured **content blocks** (`type: text`, ŌĆ”) per MCP tooling responses.

Implementations **must keep request ordering + id correctness** intact; do not mutate framing when wrapping `spawn()`.

### Tools you ship here

- **`run_rtk_command`** (`extras/mcp-rtk-server/src/index.ts`): required string **`command`** ŌåÆ tokenizes with **`shell-quote` parse** ŌåÆ `spawn(RTK_CLI_PATH)` default **`/usr/local/bin/rtk`**.

## Debugging checklist

| Symptom | Likelihood |
|---------|-------------|
| Server exits immediately | Unhandled rejection before `StdioServerTransport` bindŌĆöcheck MCP Logs. |
| Tool never registers | Older SDK mismatchŌĆöcompare `@modelcontextprotocol/server` release notes vs Cursor version. |
| `rtk` ENOENT | Install CLI (`scripts/install-rtk.sh`) or export **`RTK_CLI_PATH`**. |

